You need two pieces: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` and **BackButtonBehavior** on the page.

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on EditProductPage

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage ...>
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- rest of your form -->
</ContentPage>
```

```csharp
// In your ViewModel
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    if (HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 2. Guard the hardware/gesture back (Android swipe, etc.)

The custom `BackButtonBehavior` only handles the **toolbar** back button. The system back gesture bypasses it, so you also need `OnNavigating` in `AppShell`:

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **`args.GetDeferral()`** is required because `DisplayAlert` is async — without it the navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- **`args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop`** ensures the guard only fires on back navigation, not on forward pushes.
- The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles the toolbar button; `OnNavigating` catches the system back gesture. To avoid a double-prompt, you can set a flag in the VM (e.g., `SkipGuard = true`) before calling `GoToAsync("..")` in the command, and check it in `OnNavigating`.
